\begin_inset Formula $\hat{\theta},$
\end_inset

 is the maximizer of
\begin_inset Formula
\begin{eqnarray}
s_{n}(\theta) & = & \frac{1}{n}\sum_{i=1}^{n}\left(y_{i}\ln p(x_{i},\theta)+(1-y_{i})\ln\left[1-p(x_{i},\theta)\right]\right)\nonumber \\
 & \equiv & \frac{1}{n}\sum_{i=1}^{n}s(y_{i},x_{i},\theta).\label{s(y,A...)}
\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset

